<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 2em;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .orientation-info {
            background: #f0f8ff;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .orientation-demo {
            background: #fff;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            padding: 2em;
            margin: 2em 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        @media print {
            body {
                margin: 0;
            }
            <% if (landscape) { %>
            @page {
                size: landscape;
            }
            <% } else { %>
            @page {
                size: portrait;
            }
            <% } %>
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1><%= title %></h1>

    <div class="orientation-info">
        <h2>Page Orientation Test</h2>
        <p><strong>Current orientation:</strong> <%= landscape ? 'Landscape' : 'Portrait' %></p>
        <p>This page is configured to print in <strong><%= landscape ? 'landscape' : 'portrait' %></strong> mode.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="orientation-demo">
        <h2>Orientation Visualization</h2>
        <% if (landscape) { %>
        <p>üìÑ ‚ÜîÔ∏è This page should be wider than it is tall (landscape)</p>
        <p>The page width should be greater than the page height.</p>
        <% } else { %>
        <p>üìÑ ‚ÜïÔ∏è This page should be taller than it is wide (portrait)</p>
        <p>The page height should be greater than the page width.</p>
        <% } %>

        <div style="margin: 2em 0;">
            <div style="display: inline-block; width: 100px; height: 50px; background: #ddd; border: 1px solid #999; margin: 10px;">
                Width: 100px<br>Height: 50px<br><small>(Landscape box)</small>
            </div>
            <div style="display: inline-block; width: 50px; height: 100px; background: #ddd; border: 1px solid #999; margin: 10px;">
                <div style="writing-mode: vertical-lr; text-align: center; padding: 10px; font-size: 10px;">
                    Width: 50px Height: 100px (Portrait box)
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="orientation-info">
        <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
        <p>Use this page to test:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>CSS @page orientation directives</li>
            <li>How Printeer handles landscape vs portrait orientation</li>
            <li>Whether the orientation parameter is properly applied</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Expected behavior:</strong> The generated PDF should respect the specified orientation.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>